    "shortDescription": "Great white sharks are the largest predatory fish on Earth, and they are bristling with senses — they can detect a single drop of blood spread through thousands of liters of seawater. They roll their eyes back in their heads just before biting to protect them. Fun fact: Great white sharks can detect the tiny electrical field generated by another animal's heartbeat, using organs called ampullae of Lorenzini."
